HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 42
BY REPRESENTATIVES DEVILLIER AND FREEMAN AND SENATOR HENRY
COMMENDATIONS: Commends David Kerstein on being awarded the 2025 Times-
Picayune Loving Cup
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend David Kerstein for being awarded the 2025 Times-Picayune Loving Cup.
3 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize David Kerstein for his philanthropic
4 contributions to the city of New Orleans and to commend him for being awarded the 2025
5 Times-Picayune Loving Cup; and
6 WHEREAS, Mr. Kerstein is a lawyer, oil-company executive, and philanthropist
7 who works to make art accessible to all citizens and to preserve the New Orleans institutions
8 that provide integral support for this endeavor; and
9 WHEREAS, Mr. Kerstein is a native of Eunice, Louisiana, and graduated from the
10 city's public schools; he moved to New Orleans to attend Tulane University, where he earned
11 his undergraduate and law degrees; and
12 WHEREAS, Mr. Kerstein is the head of the Helis Foundation, which is a
13 philanthropic force in New Orleans that awarded nearly $2.4 million in grants in 2024; in
14 this role, he helped WWOZ-FM find a new home, installed public sculptures along Poydras
15 Street, established admission-free events at museums for Louisiana residents, and created
16 a sculpture garden in City Park to showcase the works of Mexican-born New Orleans artist
17 Enrique Alférez; and
18 WHEREAS, this year, Mr. Kerstein and the Helis Foundation have been major
19 supporters of the Louisiana artists who have been selected to participate in the Venice
20 Biennale; the event will showcase the state's artistic talent at one of the world's foremost
21 cultural exhibitions; and
